An NGO has said the ODM party nominations were biased.Haki Africa said the ODM primaries were disorganised and &ldquo;full of malpractices&rdquo;.The NGO was accredited by the IEBC to observe the primaries and elections across the six Coast counties - Mombasa, Tana River, Kilifi, Kwale, Lamu and Taita Taveta.Executive director Hussein Khalid said the ODM primaries were manipulated &ldquo;and this led to numerous complaints by aspirants and voters&rdquo;.ODM nominations conducted on Saturday were marred by chaos as goons destroyed voting materials.Changamwe MP Omar Mwinyi was among those arrested for alleged election malpractices.He is expected to face charges at the Mombasa law courts after his plea-taking was deferred.